  <cite><strong>Kian</strong> </cite> said 2 days later:<br />
  <p>I just use Quicken (not even QuickBooks). It&#8217;s still pretty easy to set up accounts and categories to track income and expenses from the consulting gig.</p>


	<p>Just try to set up your expense categories to be similar to the ones in Section II of the Schedule C (if you&#8217;re a sole proprietor). Then you can run reports at tax-time and just plop the numbers right in.</p>


	<p>I used to use an accountant, but now how found that TurboTax Premier does a fine job for a one-man shop.</p>
